      {{#> column-layout--default includeGlossary=true}}
        <p>When people and companies come to <em class="glossary__term">futures exchanges</em> to buy and sell <em class="glossary__term" data-term="commodity">commodities</em> and financial products, what they’re really trying to do is remove <em class="glossary__term" data-term="risk">risk</em> from their business or make money as an investor when prices fluctuate. Bottom line, they don’t know the future. But <em class="glossary__term" data-term="derivative">derivatives</em> like <em class="glossary__term" data-term="future">futures</em> and <em class="glossary__term" data-term="option">options</em> can help them protect their goals, even if prices move in the wrong direction.</p>
